WARRI  – The Bible Society of Nigeria in the spirit of Easter and the need topropagatethegospel of Christ to mankind in general, recently presented the Easter Package of GospelMaterialstothePresiden­cy in Aso Rock Villa. Presenting the package, on behalf of the patron, Bible Society of Nigeria (BSN), Ni­geria’s former Head of State, Gen. Yakubu Gowon, and the General Secretary/CEO, Bible Society of Nigeria (BSN) Pastor Samuel Sanusi, Hon. Ambassa­dor Patrick Okpomu who deliv­ered the materials said it was a privilege and honour to formal­ly present BSN’s Easter Pack­age of Gospel Materials to his dear friend and con­fidant, Pastor Femi Adesina, Special Adviser to the Pres­ident of the Federal Republic of Nigeria on Media & Publicity at the inner chamber of the Presidential Villa, Aso Rock, Abu­ja. Hon. Okpomu stated that they had a fruitful deliberation on issues of utmost national importance bordering on Eco­nomic Development, Security, Youth Empowerment, Niger Delta Development, Foreign Relations/Global Politics etc. Okpomu added that he would continue to deploy his global network and contacts for national goals and objectives as part of his service to God, hu­manity and the nation. He commended Pastor Ade­sina, the Presidential Aide for the warm reception given to him during the visit to saying, “I appreciate the special treat and warm reception accorded me, l assure the Presidency of the continuous support by the Bible Society of Nigeria in every way possible to take our nation to the next level of greatness.